The paper deals with information-theoretic metrics and their applications in the analysis of learning algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), or Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories. However, since the focus is on information-theoretic bounds and their applications in learning algorithms, cs.IT and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories.
